    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-08T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-08T06:30:00-05:00" n="736"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–852: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d736fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        Karachi and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-08T17:00:00+05:30"
                            >August 8, 1952—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>562. I have considered suggestion made in Karachi’s tel 173 to <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>, rptd Delhi 28,<note n="2" xml:id="d736fn2">
                        <ref target="#d735">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> in response <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 173 to
                    Karachi, rptd Delhi 325, and have formed conclusion less said here now the
                    better. In any case I doubt whether representations wld influence <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> who has decided views on issues, which he
                    has already anticipated in recent parliamentary debates. Therefore, as far as
                        <gloss target="#t_IN1">Ind</gloss> concerned I suggest problem be left with
                        <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> and US for time being.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
